github: https://github.com/JulianZhan/gnn-starter kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/gan-getting-started/overview

Introduction¶

In this notebook, the goal is to generate images in the style of Monet using GANs. The dataset includes Monet images and normal photos that will be used to train the GAN.

I will create a generator that produces Monet-style images from photos and a discriminator to distinguish between real Monet images and generated images.

Data Description¶

The dataset is structured as follows:

  • Monet images: monet_jpg/*.jpg
  • Photo images: photo_jpg/*.jpg

Data Visualization¶

The images are preprocessed by resizing them and normalizing the pixel values. Then, visualize a few samples from the Monet and photo datasets to get an idea of the image style.

In [3]:
def load_and_preprocess_image(image_path):
    image = tf.io.read_file(image_path)
    image = tf.image.decode_jpeg(image, channels=3)
    image = tf.image.convert_image_dtype(image, tf.float32)  
    image = tf.image.resize(image, [256, 256])
    return image

def display_jpg_samples(image_paths, num_samples=5):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))
    for i, image_path in enumerate(image_paths[:num_samples]):
        image = load_and_preprocess_image(image_path)
        plt.subplot(1, num_samples, i + 1)
        plt.imshow(image)
        plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()

display_jpg_samples(monet_jpg_path)
display_jpg_samples(photo_jpg_path)
In [4]:
def create_dataset(image_paths, batch_size=1, buffer_size=1000):
    dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(image_paths)
    dataset = dataset.map(load_and_preprocess_image, num_parallel_calls=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
    dataset = dataset.shuffle(buffer_size).batch(batch_size).prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
    return dataset

monet_dataset = create_dataset(monet_jpg_path)
photo_dataset = create_dataset(photo_jpg_path)

display_jpg_samples(monet_jpg_path)
display_jpg_samples(photo_jpg_path)

Model Architecture¶

The CycleGAN model architecture consists of 2 generators and 2 discriminators.

  1. The generators transform images between the photo and Monet domains.
    1. The discriminators distinguish between real and generated images.
In [5]:
def generator_model():
    inputs = Input(shape=(256, 256, 3))
    outputs = Conv2D(3, (7, 7), padding='same', activation='tanh')(inputs)
    return Model(inputs, outputs)

def discriminator_model():
    inputs = Input(shape=(256, 256, 3))
    outputs = Conv2D(1, (4, 4), strides=(2, 2), padding='same')(inputs)
    return Model(inputs, outputs)

monet_generator = generator_model()
photo_generator = generator_model()
monet_discriminator = discriminator_model()
photo_discriminator = discriminator_model()

Loss Functions and Optimizers¶

We use the Adam optimizer for all models training. The loss functions are defined as follows:

  1. CycleGAN loss: Measures the difference between the real and generated images.
  2. Discriminator loss: Measures the difference between the real and generated outputs of the discriminator
In [6]:
def cycle_gan_loss(real, generated):
    return tf.reduce_mean(tf.abs(real - generated))

def discriminator_loss(real_output, generated_output):
    real_loss = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy()(tf.ones_like(real_output), real_output)
    generated_loss = tf.keras.losses.BinaryCrossentropy()(tf.zeros_like(generated_output), generated_output)
    total_loss = real_loss + generated_loss
    return total_loss

monet_generator_optimizer = Adam(2e-4, beta_1=0.5)
photo_generator_optimizer = Adam(2e-4, beta_1=0.5)
monet_discriminator_optimizer = Adam(2e-4, beta_1=0.5)
photo_discriminator_optimizer = Adam(2e-4, beta_1=0.5)
In [7]:
@tf.function
def train_step(real_monet, real_photo):
    with tf.GradientTape(persistent=True) as tape:
        fake_photo = monet_generator(real_monet, training=True)
        cycled_monet = photo_generator(fake_photo, training=True)
        fake_monet = photo_generator(real_photo, training=True)
        cycled_photo = monet_generator(fake_monet, training=True)

        disc_real_monet = monet_discriminator(real_monet, training=True)
        disc_fake_monet = monet_discriminator(fake_monet, training=True)
        disc_real_photo = photo_discriminator(real_photo, training=True)
        disc_fake_photo = photo_discriminator(fake_photo, training=True)

        gen_monet_loss = cycle_gan_loss(real_photo, fake_photo)
        gen_photo_loss = cycle_gan_loss(real_monet, fake_monet)
        total_cycle_loss = gen_monet_loss + gen_photo_loss

        monet_disc_loss = discriminator_loss(disc_real_monet, disc_fake_monet)
        photo_disc_loss = discriminator_loss(disc_real_photo, disc_fake_photo)

    monet_generator_gradients = tape.gradient(total_cycle_loss, monet_generator.trainable_variables)
    photo_generator_gradients = tape.gradient(total_cycle_loss, photo_generator.trainable_variables)
    monet_discriminator_gradients = tape.gradient(monet_disc_loss, monet_discriminator.trainable_variables)
    photo_discriminator_gradients = tape.gradient(photo_disc_loss, photo_discriminator.trainable_variables)

    monet_generator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(monet_generator_gradients, monet_generator.trainable_variables))
    photo_generator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(photo_generator_gradients, photo_generator.trainable_variables))
    monet_discriminator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(monet_discriminator_gradients, monet_discriminator.trainable_variables))
    photo_discriminator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(photo_discriminator_gradients, photo_discriminator.trainable_variables))

Training¶

Run the training loop and updating the progress bar for each batch to track the training progress.

In [8]:
from tqdm import tqdm

epochs = 10
for epoch in range(epochs):
    with tqdm(total=len(monet_dataset), desc=f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}", unit="batch") as pbar:
        for step, (monet_image, photo_image) in enumerate(tf.data.Dataset.zip((monet_dataset, photo_dataset))):
            train_step(monet_image, photo_image)
            pbar.update(1)
    print(f"Epoch {epoch+1} completed")

output_dir = '/kaggle/generated_images'

for i, image in enumerate(tqdm(generated_images, desc="Saving images", unit="image")):
    image = tf.squeeze(image, axis=0) 
    image = tf.image.convert_image_dtype(image, dtype=tf.uint8)
    tf.io.write_file(f'{output_dir}/image_{i}.jpg', tf.image.encode_jpeg(image))
